\h #dBANPC \d

\uUSAGE\n
#dbanpc \s[\dname reason\s]\d

\uDESCRIPTION\n
Dump the banned PC database, or ban/unban a PC.
When no arguments are provided, every record in the database is displayed.
To add a new record to the database (effectively toggling between banned/unbanned status), provide the full name of the PC you wish to ban/unban, followed by a description of the reason.
If you ban a player who is currently logged in, he/she will be booted immediately.

\uEXAMPLES\n
\q#dbanpc\d to dump the database.4`
\q#dbanpc taro for harassment\d to ban Taro.4`
\q#dbanpc taro the team decided to give him another chance\d to unban Taro.4`

\uSEE ALSO\n
